# 🐬 MySQL Installation Guide (DB Tier Setup)

## 🎯 Objective

This guide explains how to install and configure MySQL database server on an AWS EC2 instance in the private subnet as part of a 3-tier architecture.

---

## 🧱 Architecture Context

MySQL is part of the Database Tier:

Nginx → Tomcat → MySQL

---

## 🖥️ Prerequisites

Before installation ensure:
- EC2 instance is launched in private subnet
- Security group allows port 3306 only from Tomcat SG
- SSH access via Bastion/NAT is available
- Linux OS (Amazon Linux / RHEL)

---

## 📦 Step 1: Update System Packages

```bash
sudo yum update -y

Step 2: Install MySQL Server
sudo yum install mysql-server -y
🚀 Step 3: Start and Enable MySQL Service
sudo systemctl start mysqld
sudo systemctl enable mysqld
🔍 Step 4: Check MySQL Service Status
sudo systemctl status mysqld
🔐 Step 5: Secure MySQL Installation
sudo mysql_secure_installation
Follow prompts:
Set root password
Remove anonymous users
Disallow root remote login
Remove test database
Reload privilege tables
🗄️ Step 6: Login to MySQL
mysql -u root -p
🧾 Step 7: Create Application Database
CREATE DATABASE appdb;
👤 Step 8: Create Application User
CREATE USER 'appuser'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'App@12345';
🔐 Step 9: Grant Privileges
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON appdb.* TO 'appuser'@'%';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
🌐 Step 10: Configure MySQL for Remote Access

Open configuration file:

sudo vi /etc/my.cnf

Update:

bind-address = 127.0.0.1

To:

bind-address = 0.0.0.0
🔄 Step 11: Restart MySQL Service
sudo systemctl restart mysqld
